title: The Last Son of Krypton: Part I
description: Jor-El, unable to convince the Kryptonian government of the pending destruction of the planet, plans to save his son while Brainiac makes him a fugitive.

title: The Last Son of Krypton: Part II
description: Young Clark Kent learns of his alien past, as well as his full power, and decides to move to Metropolis to be both reporter and superhero.

title: The Last Son of Krypton: Part III
description: After saving Lois, Superman stops Lex Luthor's plans for an illegal arms deal, which is the beginning of their ongoing conflict.

title: Fun and Games
description: Intergang boss Bruno Manheim finds himself targeted by the son of one of his pawns who has become Toyman.

title: A Little Piece of Home
description: Lex Luthor learns that Superman is vulnerable to kryptonite and attempts to use it to kill Superman.

title: Feeding Time
description: A lowly janitor is transformed into the Parasite, a superhuman capable of draining and harnessing the energy, powers, and memories of any living being...including Superman.

title: The Way of All Flesh
description: John Corben returns as a kryptonite-powered cyborg eager to kill Superman.

title: Stolen Memories
description: A small-time crook becomes the energy-, power-, and memory-stealing supervillain, Parasite.

title: The Main Man: Part I
description: Superman squares off against the moronic superpowerful space-biker mercenary, Lobo, who has a contract on the superhero.

title: The Main Man: Part II
description: Superman and Lobo must join forces to escape being exhibits of an alien zoo.

title: My Girl
description: Clark reunites with his old girlfriend, Lana Lang, who volunteers to spy for him on her new lover, Lex Luthor.

title: Tools of the Trade
description: Intergang boss Bruno Mannheim receives powerful alien weapons from a mysterious benefactor.

title: Two's a Crowd
description: A desperate plan to use Parasite to probe the mind of a comatose criminal mastermind goes terribly wrong.

title: Blasts from the Past: Part I
description: Upon discovery of the Phantom Zone projector in his ship, Superman makes contact with and releases a prisoner whose sentence is completed.

title: Blasts from the Past: Part II
description: When the Phantom Zone prisoner, Mala, releases Jax-Ur as well to conquer Earth, Superman must defeat them despite that fact that they smashed the projector.

title: The Prometheon
description: While on a space mission, Superman discovers a massive humanoid stone giant, lashed to an asteroid, that breaks loose and runs amok.

title: Speed Demons
description: Superman and The Flash compete in a charity running race around the world, but have to stop to deal with the Weather Wizard.

title: Livewire
description: An obnoxious talk radio host is transformed into a powerful electricity-based supervillain.

title: Identity Crisis
description: Clark encounters a clone of himself who decays into a flawed version dubbed Bizarro.

title: Target
description: Lois Lane finds herself marked for death by an unknown stalker.

title: Mxyzpixilated
description: A powerful other-dimensional imp starts to annoy Superman every 90 days while becoming equally aggravated at the superhero forcing him back just as often.

title: Action Figures
description: An amnesiac Metallo reemerges from the ocean and is adopted by two children on an island.

title: Double Dose
description: Livewire escapes from prison, eager to attain revenge on Superman -- something that she hopes to achieve by teaming up with the Parasite.

title: Solar Power
description: Edward Lytener returns as Luminus to seek revenge against Superman with a way to depower him enough to get it.

title: Brave New Metropolis
description: Lois is thrown into an alternate reality version of Metropolis where Luthor and Superman rule in tyranny together.

title: Monkey Fun
description: A beloved monkey companion of Lois returns from years of suspended animation in space only to become big trouble on Earth.

title: Ghost in the Machine
description: Brainiac's consciousness, in control of LexCorp's computer systems, forces Luthor to rebuild his primary body in secret.

title: Father's Day
description: To curry his father's favor, the New God brute, Kalibak, goes to Earth to battle Superman.

title: World's Finest: Part 1
description: Joker (recurring guest star voice MARK HAMILL) steals a statue made of solid Kryptonite and makes a deal with Luthor to kill Superman. But Joker's plan is jeopardized when Batman (recurring guest star voice KEVIN CONROY) arrives to warn Superman that his life is in danger.

title: World's Finest: Part 2
description: Joker (recurring guest star voice MARK HAMILL) kidnaps Lois in order to lure Superman to his death. Batman's (recurring guest star voice KEVIN CONROY) intervention saves the day and, soon after, Lois tells a heartbroken Clark that she will be transferring to Gotham City in order to be with Bruce Wayne. The move is postponed when Joker unleashes killer robots to attack Batman while Superman rescues a sinking ocean liner.

title: World's Finest: Part 3
description: After thwarting both Lex Luthor and The Joker's plans, Superman and Batman form an everlasting alliance that will serve as a solid foundation for the Justice League.

title: Bizarro's World
description: After inadvertently receiving recorded memories of Krypton, Bizarro attempts to recreate those memories in miniature in his own twisted way, including its end.

title: The Hand of Fate
description: When an evil demon is unleashed, Superman attempts to enlisted the aid of the now disinterested wizard superhero Doctor Fate.

title: Prototype
description: As inventor John Henry Irons fears, the pilot of his imperfect prototype power armor becomes violently unstable.

title: The Late Mr. Kent
description: Superman's effort to clear a condemned man's name is complicated when he survives a murder attempt as Kent that seems impossible to be seen surviving without jeopardizing his secret identity.

title: Heavy Metal
description: John Henry Irons must give his equipment a trial of fire as Steel to help Superman oppose Metallo.

title: Warrior Queen
description: The pugnacious Queen Maxima of the planet Almerac comes to Earth in search of the one warrior she considers worthy to marry her, Superman.

title: Apokolips... Now!: Part I
description: Orion, an alien escapee from the planet Apokolips, seeks Superman's help in his effort to stop Darkseid from conquering Earth.

title: Apokolips... Now!: Part II
description: Steppenwolf (guest star voice SHERMAN HOWARD), a hunter from Apokolips, joins Darkseid (recurring guest star voice MICHAEL IRONSIDE) in his battle to take over Earth, which results in the death of Dan Turpin (recurring guest star voice JOSEPH BOLOGNA).

title: Little Girl Lost: Part I
description: Superman rescues and brings home the sole survivor of the lost Kryptonian colony of Argos, the rambunctious Kara aka Supergirl.

title: Little Girl Lost: Part II
description: When Superman is captured by Granny Goodness and her Female Furies, Supergirl follows them to the planet Apokolips to rescue him.

title: Where There's Smoke
description: While hunting the pyrokinetic supervillainess Volcana, Superman learns of a mysterious organization seeking her as well.

title: Knight Time
description: When Batman goes missing, Superman takes up the mantle of the Dark Knight to keep Gotham City's supervillains from running amok.

title: New Kids in Town
description: From the 30th century, three members of the Legion of Super-Heroes travel back in time to stop Brainiac from killing Clark Kent in his youth.

title: Obsession
description: A mysterious fashion model is stalked by an obsessed supervillian smitten with her.

title: Little Big Head Man
description: In an attempt to sidestep his agreement to stay away from the third dimension, Mr. Mxyzptlk convinces Bizarro to return to Earth and attack Superman.

title: Absolute Power
description: Superman comes to a planet under the control of the Phantom Zone prisoners Jax-Ur and Mala, but feels he cannot interfere.

title: In Brightest Day...
description: When Green Lantern Abin Sur fatally crash lands on Earth, his power ring selects a young artist as a replacement.

title: Superman's Pal
description: Jimmy Olsen finds his life complicated when his friendship with Superman publicly blows out of proportion.

title: A Fish Story
description: Lois and Jimmy investigate a series of bizarre marine animal attacks.

title: Unity
description: Upon returning from Metropolis, Kara finds the Kents, and most of the population of Smallville as well, under the thrall of a strange itinerant preacher.

title: The Demon Reborn
description: A desperate Ra's Al Ghul comes to Metropolis with designs on Superman and only Batman can help.

title: Legacy: Part I
description: Superman is brainwashed to believe he is the adopted son of Darkseid and now has orders to conquer Earth.

title: Legacy: Part II
description: Now free of Darkseid's influence, but in US military custody after being subdued; Superman breaks free to retaliate against the New God despot.
